column1: CAUSE OF DEATH  IN LONG ASHTON UNION AND REGISTRATION DISTRICT (1901 â€“ 1920)
From 1911 Long Ashton Poor Law Union comprised the registration districts of Long Ashton Rural District; Clevedon Urban
District; and Portishead Urban District. After 1920 data were only given for registration districts with a population over 10,000,
and thus Portishead and Clevedon were no longer included. Only the data for Long Ashton district within the union were still
